              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-1b1117a2-8882-4caa-93d3-696fb2e82b17');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",

          "name": "stderr",
          "text": [
            "<ipython-input-10-51664e56ba2f>:2: FutureWarning: A value is trying to be set on a copy of a DataFrame or Series through chained assignment using an inplace method.\n",
            "The behavior will change in pandas 3.0. This inplace method will never work because the intermediate object on which we are setting values always behaves as a copy.\n",
            "\n",
            "For example, when doing 'df[col].method(value, inplace=True)', try using 'df.method({col: value}, inplace=True)' or df[col] = df[col].method(value) instead, to perform the operation inplace on the original object.\n",
            "\n",
            "\n",
            "  aerodreams_data['Arrival Delay in Minutes'].fillna(aerodreams_data['Arrival Delay in Minutes'].median(), inplace=True)\n"
          ]
        }

        "# Import necessary libraries\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, roc_curve"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ywu5xfisHAVP"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Step 1: Train the Random Forest Model\n",
        "rf_model = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "r88T_wwAHAR0"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Define hyperparameter grid\n",
        "param_grid_rf = {\n",
        "    'n_estimators': [100, 200],\n",
        "    'max_depth': [10, 20],\n",
        "    'min_samples_split': [2, 5]\n",
        "}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wCsn4BBNHAOw"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Perform hyperparameter tuning using GridSearchCV\n",
        "grid_rf = GridSearchCV(rf_model, param_grid_rf, cv=3, scoring='accuracy', n_jobs=-1)\n",
        "grid_rf.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "best_rf = grid_rf.best_estimator_"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "M2sAV-jDHALk"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Step 2: Validate performance using the validation dataset\n",
        "y_pred_rf = best_rf.predict(X_val)\n",
        "y_prob_rf = best_rf.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]  # For ROC-AUC calculation"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "V0T_Q-wmHAIY"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Step 3: Evaluate Model Performance\n",
        "accuracy_rf = accuracy_score(y_val, y_pred_rf)\n",
        "classification_report_rf = classification_report(y_val, y_pred_rf)\n",
        "conf_matrix_rf = confusion_matrix(y_val, y_pred_rf)\n",
        "roc_auc_rf = roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_rf)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Bu0Ifh6SHAFc"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },

        "from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, log_loss, roc_curve"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "lXYABr_EK7Wa"

      "metadata": {
        "id": "-cu4Iy4LK7TL"

      "outputs": []

        "# Define hyperparameter grid for tuning\n",
        "param_grid_dt = {\n",
        "    'max_depth': [5, 10, 20],\n",
        "    'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10],\n",
        "    'criterion': ['gini', 'entropy']\n",
        "}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Am5M28V9K7Pc"

      "outputs": []

      "source": [
        "# Perform hyperparameter tuning using GridSearchCV\n",
        "grid_dt = GridSearchCV(\n",
        "    estimator=DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42),\n",
        "    param_grid=param_grid_dt,\n",
        "    cv=3,\n",
        "    scoring='accuracy',\n",
        "    n_jobs=-1\n",
        ")\n",
        "grid_dt.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "best_dt = grid_dt.best_estimator_"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qmwuKfjRG_18"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []

        "y_prob_dt = best_dt.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]  # For ROC-AUC calculation\n"
